MCP Onboarding
This guide covers how to onboard your remote MCP server into Agency so it becomes available as a built-in MCP for all Agency users.

Prerequisites
Before submitting your MCP for onboarding, ensure:

Your MCP is a remote (HTTPS) server — Agency only onboards remote MCPs, not local executables. Remote MCPs provide centralized auth, lower startup cost, and consistent behavior across local CLI and Azure DevOps pipelines.
Your MCP uses Entra ID authentication — Agency handles token acquisition automatically via the WWW-Authenticate challenge flow. Your server must return HTTP 401 with a WWW-Authenticate header for unauthenticated requests.
You have tested your MCP with Agency — Use agency mcp remote to validate authentication, schema compatibility, and tool registration before onboarding. See Testing Your Remote MCP for details.
Onboarding Process
Step 1: Test Your MCP
Follow the Testing Your Remote MCP guide to verify your MCP works with Agency. At a minimum, confirm:

Authentication works (tokens acquired and accepted)
All tools register successfully (no schema validation failures)
Tool calls return valid responses
Step 2: Submit the Onboarding Form
Fill out the MCP onboarding intake form:

➡️ MCP Onboarding Form

The form requires the following information:

Field	Description
MCP Name	Lowercase, kebab-case name for your MCP as it will appear in Agency (e.g., icm, kusto, es-chat)
Remote URL	The full HTTPS URL of your MCP endpoint
Entra Client ID	The Entra app registration client ID your server pre-authorizes (leave blank to use the default Azure CLI client ID)
Team Contacts	Email aliases or distribution lists for the owning team
Support Link	URL to your support channel, documentation, or help alias
Area Path	Your team's Azure DevOps area path
ICM Path	The ICM routing path for incidents related to your MCP
Service Tree ID	Your service's Service Tree identifier
Step 3: Review and Onboarding
After form submission, the Agency team will:

Review your MCP for compatibility and security
Coordinate with your team on any required changes
Add your MCP to Agency's built-in server list
Update documentation and release
What Gets Onboarded
Once onboarded, your MCP becomes available to all Agency users via:

# As a CLI flag
agency copilot --mcp <your-mcp-name>

# As a standalone MCP server
agency mcp <your-mcp-name>
It also becomes configurable in .vscode/mcp.json, ~/.copilot/mcp-config.json, and custom agent frontmatter. See Agency MCP Servers for full configuration details.

